<body>
<div class="main">
<h1>AS4242421080 Peering</h2>
{% include 'navigation.j2' %}
<div id="container">

<h2 id="peering-info">
    <i class="fa fa-random" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    Peering Info
</h2>
    <p>To set up peering, feel free to reach out via IRC (jlu5), <a href="https://t.me/jlu5ca">Telegram</a>, or <a href="mailto:james@overdrivenetworks.com">email</a>. These PoPs support WireGuard (preferred) and OpenVPN.</p>
    <p>For consistency, I prefer multiprotocol BGP sessions over IPv6. For WireGuard + BIRD users, I recommend using <strong>link-local IPv6 addresses</strong>, and <strong>ULA IPv6 addresses</strong> if you‚Äôre using OpenVPN or any other BGP daemon (there are some interoperability issues). Note: <strong>I will usually set up WireGuard with link-local addresses unless you mention otherwise</strong>.</p>
    <p>If you have multiple nodes, especially across multiple continents, I also recommend setting up multiple links to improve redundancy and encourage the most direct routing.</p>
    <p>Note: my publicly visible <a href="https://github.com/jlu5/ansible-dn42">config repo</a> includes the endpoint info for most of my peers. If you would like to keep this private, please let me know when submitting your peering request.</p>
    <p>OpenVPN peers should send me their static keys via PGP-encrypted mail (<a href="https://keys.openpgp.org/search?q=D5D568B2D34AB32A337944D22EC3F60DE71C0B9D">D5D568B2D34AB32A337944D22EC3F60DE71C0B9D</a>) or some other secure medium.</p>

<h2 id="recent-changes">
    <i class="fa fa-newspaper-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    Recent Changes
</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>2021-07-24</strong>: the default peering port has been moved from 5xxxx to 2xxxx to avoid conflicts with the default <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ephemeral_port">ephemeral port range</a> on Linux. Existing peers are unchanged for now.</li>
    </ul>

<h2 id="nodes">
    <i class="fa fa-server" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    Nodes
</h2>

{% macro peering_info(host) %}
{% set serverdata = hostvars[host] %}
{% set link_slug = serverdata.location.replace(',', '').replace(' ', '-') | lower %}
<h4 id="{{ link_slug }}">
    {{ serverdata.location[-2:] | flag }} {{ serverdata.location }}
    <a href="#{{ link_slug }}"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hostname</strong>: {{ host }}</li>
    <li><strong>WireGuard / OpenVPN port</strong>: 20000 + last 4 digits of your ASN</li>
    <li><strong>WireGuard pubkey</strong>: {{ serverdata.wg_pubkey }}</li>
    <li><strong>Tunneled IPv4 address</strong>: {{ serverdata.ownip }}</li>
    <li><strong>Tunneled IPv6 address</strong>: {{ serverdata.link_local_ip6 }} (link-local) OR {{ serverdata.ownip6 }}</li>
</ul>
{% endmacro %}

<h3 id="americas">üåé Americas</h3>
{% for host in groups['us'] + groups['sa'] %}
{{ peering_info(host) }}
{% endfor %}

<h3 id="europe">üåç Europe</h3>
{% for host in groups['eu'] %}
{{ peering_info(host) }}
{% endfor %}

<h3 id="apac">üåè Asia Pacific</h3>
